abstract: |
Purity UI Control Architecture v0.1 is a draft specification for designing
creator-controlled user interfaces that preserve, display, and govern
human-origin epicenters in AI-mediated platforms.

This specification extends the concept of Purity beyond scoring. It focuses
on how creators can control epicenter visibility, unresolved friction,
question structure, meaning boundaries, AI inference permissions, trace
visibility, royalty-readiness previews, circle versioning, platform-level
disclosure controls, and epicenter network relationships.

The goal is not to judge creators or rank works by purity. The goal is to
give creators control over how their human-origin meaning structures are
displayed, accessed, interpreted, and reused in AI ecosystems.

This specification is related to AI Purity Detection Algorithm v0.2, but it
defines a separate UI-control and creator-sovereignty layer rather than a
scoring or review-routing algorithm.
